issues.description:
In `src/cli/commands/serve.ts` lines 64-68:
```ts
const code = (e as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code;
if (code !== "ESRCH") {
  // Process no longer exists — fine, proceed to start
  logDashboard(`dashboard: takeover kill failed (${code}) — proceeding`);
}
```
The comment says 'Process no longer exists — fine, proceed to start' but ESRCH is the errno for 'no such process' (process already gone). So the `!== ESRCH` branch fires for every OTHER error (e.g. EPERM — permission denied) and logs a misleading 'takeover kill failed' message. The ESRCH case (process already gone — the normal/expected race case) gets no log at all. The plan spec (Task 1 notes) says 'kill throws ESRCH (process already gone → proceed to bind)' — meaning ESRCH should be the silent no-op, but the inverted condition means ESRCH is the case that gets silently ignored while non-ESRCH errors get logged (which is actually correct for the log part). However, the comment on the block is inverted and there's no explicit ESRCH log, violating 'all outcomes logged to dashboard.log'.

issues.suggested_fix:
Invert the condition and add explicit ESRCH logging:
```ts
const code = (e as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code;
if (code === "ESRCH") {
  logDashboard("dashboard: takeover target already gone (ESRCH) — proceeding to bind");
} else {
  logDashboard(`dashboard: takeover kill failed (${code}) — proceeding anyway`);
}
```

issues.description:
In `targets/opencode/plugins/sentinal.ts` line 171-186:
```ts
let _cachedBinaryVersion: string | null = null;
async function getBinaryVersion(): Promise<string | null> {
  if (_cachedBinaryVersion !== null) return _cachedBinaryVersion;
  // ... on failure: return null;
}
```
The sentinel for 'not yet fetched' is `null`, and the return value for 'binary not found / exec failed' is also `null`. Because the cache check is `!== null`, a failed lookup (returns `null`) is never stored and the function will re-spawn `sentinal --version` on every subsequent call. If the binary is missing or times out, the plugin will attempt to exec it on every tool call. The plan notes this should be cached 'after first call'.

issues.suggested_fix:
Use `undefined` as the 'not yet cached' sentinel:
```ts
let _cachedBinaryVersion: string | null | undefined = undefined;
async function getBinaryVersion(): Promise<string | null> {
  if (_cachedBinaryVersion !== undefined) return _cachedBinaryVersion;
  // ... compute ...
  _cachedBinaryVersion = result; // stores null on failure, caching the miss
  return _cachedBinaryVersion;
}
```

Refactor to use `else if` branches or early returns to make control flow explicit and avoid the visual implication that `takeover-no-pid` could fire after a `takeover` block:
```ts
if (decision.action === "exit") { ... process.exit(0); }
else if (decision.action === "takeover") { ... }
else if (decision.action === "takeover-no-pid") { ... process.exit(1); }
// action === "start" falls through to startServer
```
